f(x) = \sin x + \frac{\sin3x}3 + \frac{\sin5x}5 +  \frac{\sin7x}7
f' \left(\frac{\pi}{9}\right) = \frac{1}{2}
f'(x)=\cos x+\cos3x+\cos5x+\cos7x
2\sin xf'(x)=2\sin x(\cos x+\cos3x+\cos5x+\cos7x)
2\sin A\cos B=\sin(A+B)+\sin(A-B)
2\sin xf'(x)=\sin2x+\sin4x-\sin2x+\sin6x-\sin4x+\sin8x-\sin6x=\sin8x
9x=\pi, 8x=\pi-x\implies \sin8x=\sin(\pi-x)=\sin x\ne0
